WEBVTT

00:02.302 --> 00:05.304
GLENN, THINK ABOUT ALL THE TIMES
YOU'VE LIED TO US

00:05.306 --> 00:07.306
-ABOUT BEING IN FAMOUS BANDS.
-[ SIGHS ]

00:07.308 --> 00:11.110
I'VE BEEN PLAYING DRUMS
FOR SPYRO GYRA SINCE 1972!

00:11.112 --> 00:12.311
YOU GUYS KNOW
I'M IN COLDPLAY, RIGHT?

00:12.313 --> 00:13.979
DID YOU KNOW
THAT I WAS IN ARCADE FIRE?

00:13.981 --> 00:15.381
SOUNDGARDEN!
CRANBERRIES.

00:15.383 --> 00:17.082
KINGS OF LEON.
THE RUNAWAYS!

00:17.084 --> 00:19.251
SEBADOH.
WHY WON'T YOU LISTEN TO ME?

00:19.253 --> 00:20.819
I'M IN THE GOO GOO DOLLS!

00:20.821 --> 00:22.121
[ Laughing ] SEE?

00:22.123 --> 00:25.090
OKAY, BUT I'M TELLING YOU
THE TRUTH THIS TIME!

00:25.092 --> 00:27.559
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:29.796 --> 00:31.363
OH, GOD! OH, GOD!
OH, GOD!

00:31.365 --> 00:33.565
I COULD REALLY USE A HAND
IN HERE --

00:33.567 --> 00:35.734
SORRY, BUDDY,
IT'S HOAGIE TIME.

00:35.736 --> 00:37.169
OH, YEAH, SAY NO MORE!

00:37.171 --> 00:38.504
HEY, JUST CURIOUS,

00:38.506 --> 00:41.473
WHY DO YOU EAT YOUR HOAGIE
FROM THE TOP DOWN?

00:41.475 --> 00:44.643
BECAUSE, UM, THAT IS
THE ONLY WAY TO EAT A HOAGIE.

00:44.645 --> 00:45.711
[ CHUCKLES ] DUH.

00:45.713 --> 00:46.779
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

00:46.781 --> 00:48.180
OF COURSE.
I'M SO STUPID.

00:48.182 --> 00:50.549
YOU KNOW WHAT I'VE BEEN DOING,
I START AT ONE END

00:50.551 --> 00:52.818
AND I ALWAYS
JUST WORK MY WAY ACROSS.

00:52.820 --> 00:54.186
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:54.188 --> 00:56.588
I GUESS THERE'S MORE THAN
ONE WAY TO EAT A HOAGIE.

00:56.590 --> 00:58.023
[ IMITATES EXPLOSION ]

00:58.025 --> 01:01.493
OH, GOD! OH, GOD!
OH, GOD!

01:03.396 --> 01:04.663
DJ Bonebrake:
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR.

01:04.665 --> 01:05.731
♪ WORLD'S A MESS ♪

01:05.733 --> 01:09.435
♪ IT'S IN MY KISS ♪

01:09.437 --> 01:11.470
♪ THE WORLD'S A MESS,
IT'S IN MY KISS ♪

01:11.472 --> 01:13.205
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?
HOLD IT!

01:13.207 --> 01:15.774
STOP! HEY, STOP IT!

01:15.776 --> 01:18.444
WHY IS X PLAYING
IN THE NURSE'S STATION?

01:18.446 --> 01:20.979
AND, GLENN,
WHY ARE YOU BOTHERING X?

01:20.981 --> 01:23.282
SY, I'M IN X!
I'M IN X!

01:23.284 --> 01:25.184
RIGHT. LIKE YOU WERE
IN BLUES TRAVELER.

01:25.186 --> 01:26.585
Exene Cervenka:
GLENN IS IN X.

01:26.587 --> 01:28.620
HE'S BEEN SECOND BASS
SINCE 1982.

01:28.622 --> 01:30.656
YEAH, WE USUALLY REHEARSE
IN HIS PARENTS' GARAGE,

01:30.658 --> 01:32.891
BUT THEY'RE HAVING A BIG
GARAGE SALE THIS WEEKEND, SO...

01:32.893 --> 01:35.394
YEAH, I CAN'T BELIEVE THEY'RE
FINALLY SELLING THAT GARAGE.

01:35.396 --> 01:36.395
ALL RIGHT, FROM THE TOP.

01:36.397 --> 01:37.963
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR.

01:37.965 --> 01:41.133
♪♪

01:49.008 --> 01:50.309
HI, I'M FEELING OVERWHELMED

01:50.311 --> 01:52.444
ABOUT THE INFINITE NATURE
OF THE UNIVERSE,

01:52.446 --> 01:55.013
AND, WELL, I'M JUST LOOKING
FOR SOME GUIDANCE --

01:55.015 --> 01:57.149
-SHALOM, CAT.
-AS-SALAMU ALAYKUM.

01:57.151 --> 01:58.383
CATHOLIC HELLO.

01:58.385 --> 01:59.918
I'M REALLY NOT SURE
WHY I'M HERE.

01:59.920 --> 02:01.787
I MEAN, I NEVER WENT TO CHURCH
AS A KID OR ANYTHING,

02:01.789 --> 02:04.156
EXCEPT OF COURSE
ON HALLOWEEN, BUT --
YOU KNOW WHAT,

02:04.158 --> 02:06.258
WHY DON'T YOU JUST COME
WITH ME TO MY OFFICE,

02:06.260 --> 02:07.693
I'LL MAKE YOU SOME SANKA,

02:07.695 --> 02:10.795
AND WE'LL HAVE A GOOD
OLD-FASHIONED BULL SESS.

02:10.798 --> 02:13.899
♪♪

02:15.135 --> 02:16.301
[ PLAYS NOTE ]

02:16.303 --> 02:17.769
-HEY, GLENN?
-WHAT?

02:17.771 --> 02:20.105
ON THAT PART, COULD YOU PLEASE
PLAY, LIKE, LESS?

02:20.107 --> 02:21.540
EXENE,
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

02:21.542 --> 02:23.175
WHY DO I HAVE TO BE
SECOND BASS?

02:23.177 --> 02:25.244
BECAUSE YOU ARE THE SECOND BASS,
THAT'S WHY.

02:25.246 --> 02:27.513
YEAH, GLENN, YOU'VE BEEN
SECOND BASS FOR 33 YEARS.

02:27.515 --> 02:29.915
YEAH, WELL,
MAYBE I'VE BEEN UNHAPPY

02:29.917 --> 02:31.650
FOR THE LAST 33 YEARS,
JOHN!

02:31.652 --> 02:33.785
HOW COME NONE OF MY SONGS
EVER MAKE THE ALBUM.

02:33.787 --> 02:35.787
YOU KNOW, MY FRIENDS
DON'T EVEN BELIEVE ME!

02:35.789 --> 02:38.724
I MEAN, I'M STARTING TO WONDER,
WHY AM I EVEN IN THIS BAND?

02:38.726 --> 02:39.658
CAMARADERIE?

02:39.660 --> 02:41.627
AH, BILLY, CUT THE CRAP.
REALLY?

02:41.629 --> 02:43.395
GIVE ME A BREAK
ON THAT ONE.

02:43.397 --> 02:45.531
I MEAN, WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
WE ALL GOT TOGETHER FOR A DRINK?

02:45.533 --> 02:47.099
LAST NIGHT WE HAD DRINKS,
RIGHT?
Shh.

02:47.101 --> 02:48.767
-WHAT?
-NOTHING, NOTHING.

02:48.769 --> 02:50.802
I HAD ALL DAY OFF.
THAT WAS MY DAY OFF.
WE DIDN'T ASK YOU.

02:50.804 --> 02:52.638
-WE DIDN'T GO.
-I MEAN, WE DIDN'T GO.

02:52.640 --> 02:54.740
-WE DIDN'T GO.
-NO [BLEEP] YOU DIDN'T ASK ME.

02:54.742 --> 02:57.976
WELL, CAT, JUST CALL ME
PRESIDENT BARACK OBAMA,

02:57.978 --> 02:59.278
'CAUSE I'M ALL EARS.

02:59.280 --> 03:00.879
CAN WE SHAPE
OUR OWN DESTINY?

03:00.881 --> 03:04.983
I MEAN, DOES IT EVEN REALLY
MATTER HOW I EAT MY HOAGIE?

03:04.985 --> 03:07.719
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE ASKING
THE REALLY TOUGH QUESTIONS,

03:07.721 --> 03:09.955
AND THAT'S A VERY
JEWISH THING TO DO.

03:09.957 --> 03:11.490
WHAT I WANT TO KNOW,
THOUGH,

03:11.492 --> 03:13.559
IS WHY DIDN'T YOU
COME DIRECTLY TO ME?

03:13.561 --> 03:16.361
I MEAN, CATHOLICISM AND ISLAM,
I MEAN, THOSE ARE, UH,

03:16.363 --> 03:19.164
NOT REALLY SET UP FOR
THE KIND OF EXISTENTIAL INQUIRY

03:19.166 --> 03:20.799
THAT YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
INTERESTED IN.

03:20.801 --> 03:23.635
YOU KNOW, IT'S NOT THAT I AM
JUST INTERESTED IN THAT, BUT --

03:23.637 --> 03:26.038
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?
DO YOU LIKE CARAMELS?

03:26.040 --> 03:27.339
DO YOU LIKE CARAMELS?

03:27.341 --> 03:29.541
BECAUSE I'LL TELL YOU
SOMETHING --

03:29.543 --> 03:31.443
YOU DIDN'T HEAR THIS FROM ME --

03:31.445 --> 03:33.445
BUT WHEN YOU'RE JEWISH,
OKAY,

03:33.447 --> 03:36.615
YOU GET TO EAT CARAMELS
JUST LIKE THIS ALL THE TIME.

03:36.617 --> 03:39.885
HERE YOU GO, CAT.
GO AHEAD AND TAKE ONE.

03:39.887 --> 03:40.986
THAT'S IT.

03:42.455 --> 03:45.324
NO, NO, YOU GOTTA --
YOU'VE HAD CARAMELS BEFORE.

03:45.326 --> 03:46.758
YOU JUST, YEAH, UNWRAP IT.

03:46.760 --> 03:48.927
THIS IS NOT
A RELIGIOUS...

03:48.929 --> 03:50.329
EAT THE GODDAMN CANDY.

03:50.331 --> 03:53.565
X REALLY IS REHEARSING
IN THE HOSPITAL!

03:53.567 --> 03:56.235
IT SOUNDED LIKE A PREPOSTEROUS
NOTION, BUT THERE THEY ARE!

03:56.237 --> 03:58.570
♪♪

03:58.572 --> 04:00.539
GLENN,
GET AWAY FROM X!

04:00.541 --> 04:03.108
I'M IN X!
I'M PART OF THE BAND!

04:03.110 --> 04:05.177
NO, NO,
GET OUT OF THERE!

04:05.179 --> 04:07.813
ALL RIGHT, STOP!
[ WHISTLES ]

04:07.815 --> 04:09.915
STOP, STOP, STOP,
STOP, STOP.

04:09.917 --> 04:12.451
STOP, STOP, STOP,
STOP, STOP, STOP.

04:12.453 --> 04:13.852
I WANT TO DO
ONE OF MY SONGS.

04:13.854 --> 04:15.687
I THINK WE GOT TO DO
OUR TOUR SONGS.

04:15.689 --> 04:18.790
PLEASE, COME ON.
MY COWORKERS ARE WATCHING.

04:20.159 --> 04:21.159
OH...

04:21.161 --> 04:22.594
OKAY, THANK YOU.

04:24.063 --> 04:25.330
THREE, FOUR.

04:25.332 --> 04:28.767
♪♪

04:31.004 --> 04:32.971
♪ THE SUN GOES DOWN ♪

04:32.973 --> 04:36.375
♪ BUT I'M STILL UP ♪

04:36.377 --> 04:38.243
♪ DRUNK ON YOUR LOVE ♪

04:38.245 --> 04:41.213
♪ REFILL MY CUP, YEAH ♪

04:41.215 --> 04:43.148
♪ THE CLOCK STRIKES 2:00 ♪

04:43.150 --> 04:46.685
♪ AND I'M FEELIN' FREE ♪

04:46.687 --> 04:48.854
♪ GOT WONDER IN MIND ♪

04:48.856 --> 04:50.889
♪ BUT IT'S YOU ♪

04:50.891 --> 04:53.825
♪ IT'S YOU I SEE ♪

04:53.827 --> 04:57.329
♪ IT'S A LATE-NIGHT DAYDREAM ♪

04:57.331 --> 04:59.665
♪ DAYDREAM ♪

04:59.667 --> 05:04.569
♪ STRAWBERRIES, COLD CREAM,
YEAH ♪

05:04.571 --> 05:07.339
♪ YOUR LOVE
COULD KNOCK ME OVER ♪

05:07.341 --> 05:11.576
♪ BUT I STAY
ON THE BALANCE BEAM ♪

05:11.578 --> 05:13.078
♪ IT'S A LATE-NIGHT ♪

05:13.080 --> 05:14.246
♪ A LATE-NIGHT ♪

05:14.248 --> 05:18.016
♪ LATE-NIGHT DAYDREAM ♪

05:18.018 --> 05:19.084
♪ YEAH ♪

05:19.086 --> 05:21.853
GLENN,
YOU ARE RUINING X!

05:21.855 --> 05:24.756
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

05:24.758 --> 05:26.358
I HATE YOU!

05:26.360 --> 05:29.628
CATHOLICISM IS ABOUT
SERVING OTHERS, CAT.

05:29.630 --> 05:33.198
IT PUTS YOUR OWN PROBLEMS
INTO PERSPECTIVE.

05:33.200 --> 05:36.935
DID JEWY
OFFER YOU CARAMELS?

05:36.937 --> 05:39.838
YES. YES, HE DID.
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

05:39.840 --> 05:41.239
OLD DOG, OLD TRICKS.

05:41.241 --> 05:42.574
HERE'S AN OFFER --

05:42.576 --> 05:45.677
IMAGINE YOURSELF LEAVING
HERE TODAY AS A CATHOLIC

05:45.679 --> 05:51.516
AND THE PROUD OWNER
OF A $50 AMAZON GIFT CARD.

05:52.251 --> 05:53.685
WELL, LOOK!

05:53.687 --> 05:58.056
MY FRIEND BELOVED
CHARACTER ACTOR TOM ARNOLD!

05:58.058 --> 05:59.391
HELLO, FATHER.

05:59.393 --> 06:00.559
HELLO, CAT.

06:00.561 --> 06:02.260
HOW DO YOU KNOW
MY NAME?

06:02.262 --> 06:04.296
I'LL TELL YA,
THE PEOPLE YOU MEET

06:04.298 --> 06:05.964
WHEN YOU'RE A CATHOLIC,
HMM?

06:05.966 --> 06:09.167
I DON'T KNOW GUYS,
THE TEMPOS WAS SLUGGISH, OKAY?

06:09.169 --> 06:10.435
THE SOLOS WAS SLOPPY.

06:10.437 --> 06:12.404
-WE DID OUR BEST, MAN.
-HEY, GUYS,

06:12.406 --> 06:15.140
THEY'VE ASKED US TO PERFORM
ON "THE NEW DICK CAVETT SHOW."

06:15.142 --> 06:16.608
-YEAH!
-WOW.

06:16.610 --> 06:18.610
I WANT TO DO
"LATE NIGHT DAYDREAM."
NO, NO, WAIT.

06:18.612 --> 06:20.579
DON'T YOU THINK THEY WANT US
TO DO ONE OF OUR HITS?

06:20.581 --> 06:22.180
I DON'T GIVE A RAT'S ASS
WHAT THEY WANT.

06:22.182 --> 06:24.383
-THIS IS WHAT THEY NEED, JOHN!
[ PAGER BEEPS ]

06:24.385 --> 06:25.650
AH, DAMN IT.
[ SIGHS ]

06:25.652 --> 06:27.085
ALL RIGHT,
I GOTTA TAKE OUT

06:27.087 --> 06:29.454
THIS KID'S SPLEEN,
MAYBE SOME OTHER STUFF.

06:29.456 --> 06:30.689
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

06:30.691 --> 06:32.391
GET THIS CAVETT STUFF
SITUATED, ALL RIGHT?

06:32.393 --> 06:35.794
OTHERWISE, I'M SERIOUSLY GONNA
RECONSIDER MY ROLE IN THIS BAND.

06:38.030 --> 06:39.197
Cat: RED VELVET?

06:39.199 --> 06:40.966
LEMON COCONUT?

06:40.968 --> 06:42.334
OOH, RASPBERRY CRUMBLE.

06:42.336 --> 06:43.468
THIS IS HARD.

06:43.470 --> 06:44.970
SOMETIMES
THE BEST DECISION

06:44.972 --> 06:47.339
IS THE ONE
SOMEONE MAKES FOR YOU.

06:47.341 --> 06:49.040
TAKE THAT ONE.

06:49.042 --> 06:51.676
CHOCOLATE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:51.678 --> 06:54.646
YOU KNOW, FREEDOM FROM CHOICE
REALLY IS COMFORTING.

06:54.648 --> 06:56.648
ISLAM
IS A COMFORTING RELIGION.

06:56.650 --> 07:00.085
AND I CAN THROW IN
A THREE-DAY HILTON HEAD GETAWAY

07:00.087 --> 07:01.553
IF WE CLOSE THIS TODAY.

07:01.555 --> 07:03.388
SCALPEL.
PRESS THERE.

07:03.390 --> 07:04.623
ALL RIGHT, GET --

07:04.625 --> 07:07.225
THROW THE SPLEEN OUT
OR WHATEVER.

07:07.227 --> 07:09.461
HEY.
HOW CAN YOU BE DOWN, MAN?

07:09.463 --> 07:11.263
YOU JUST STOOD NEAR X!

07:11.265 --> 07:12.497
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

07:12.499 --> 07:13.799
I MEAN, SOMETIMES
I JUST FEEL LIKE

07:13.801 --> 07:15.434
I DON'T BELONG TO THAT BAND,
YOU KNOW?

07:15.436 --> 07:17.636
[ SCOFFS ]
HEY, LISTEN.

07:17.638 --> 07:19.571
YOU BELONG RIGHT HERE,

07:19.573 --> 07:22.474
SAVING THIS KID'S LIFE --
MAYBE.

07:22.476 --> 07:24.743
BECAUSE YOU'RE
GLENN RITCHIE,

07:24.745 --> 07:28.880
THE BIGGEST, BADDEST,
HOTSHOT JEW DOCTOR AT CHILDRENS.

07:28.882 --> 07:30.415
YEAH.

07:30.417 --> 07:31.616
-ALL RIGHT.
-ALL RIGHT!

07:31.618 --> 07:34.052
[ LAUGHS ]
LET'S DO THIS!

07:34.054 --> 07:35.921
-HE'S BACK!
-FIRST THING WE DO,

07:35.923 --> 07:37.589
ALL THIS FERKAKTA NONSENSE
HAS GOTTA GO!

07:37.591 --> 07:38.924
GET IT OUT!

07:38.926 --> 07:42.294
THE MOST CATHOLIC OF ALL ACTORS,
TOM ARNOLD!

07:42.296 --> 07:43.595
I'M A REAL PERSON.

07:43.597 --> 07:45.530
DO YOU WANT TO MEET
ARNOLD SCHWARZENEGGER?

07:45.532 --> 07:47.666
NOW LET'S JUST PUT
THE QUR'AN AWAY FOR A SECOND,

07:47.668 --> 07:49.501
'CAUSE I'VE GOT
A SWEET, SWEET CARAMEL.

07:49.503 --> 07:51.136
HUH, HUH?
DO YOU WANT IT?

07:51.138 --> 07:55.106
♪♪

07:56.476 --> 07:57.976
YOU HAVE PAIN.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.778
SIT.

08:03.082 --> 08:06.718
I JUST FEEL SO LOST
IN THIS WORLD.

08:06.720 --> 08:09.554
NO ANSWER
CAN TAKE AWAY YOUR PAIN.

08:09.556 --> 08:14.459
YOUR PAIN <i> IS</i> THE ANSWER.

08:14.461 --> 08:18.263
[ GASPS ]
I FINALLY GET IT.

08:18.265 --> 08:20.098
I'M A BUDDHIST.

08:20.100 --> 08:21.466
GUYS, WE NEED TO TALK.

08:21.468 --> 08:23.068
GLENN, WE NEED TO TALK.

08:23.070 --> 08:24.636
YOU GO FIRST.

08:24.638 --> 08:26.872
OKAY, UH, WE'RE KICKING YOU
OUT OF THE BAND.

08:26.874 --> 08:28.473
WOW, I SHOULD HAVE WENT FIRST.

08:28.475 --> 08:30.075
WE HAD A GOOD RUN.

08:30.077 --> 08:32.878
AND WE REALIZED THAT THE MAIN
REASON YOU'RE IN THE BAND

08:32.880 --> 08:35.547
IS SO THAT WE CAN PRACTICE
IN YOUR PARENTS' GARAGE.

08:35.549 --> 08:36.881
ALSO, WE BOUGHT THE GARAGE.

08:36.884 --> 08:41.753
LOOK, X WILL ALWAYS
BE A PART OF ME, BUT...

08:41.755 --> 08:44.155
I'M A -- I'M A DOCTOR.

08:44.157 --> 08:47.125
FIRST AND FOREMOST,
THAT'S WHO I AM.

08:47.127 --> 08:48.693
BUT I'LL MISS YOU GUYS.

08:48.695 --> 08:51.530
BILLY ZOOM, JOHN DOE,

08:51.532 --> 08:54.499
DJ BONEBRAKE,
AND EXENE CERVENKA.

08:54.501 --> 08:57.035
WHO MET JOHN DOE
AT A POETRY WORKSHOP

08:57.037 --> 08:58.370
IN VENICE, CALIFORNIA.

08:58.372 --> 08:59.871
COME ON, BRING IT IN.

08:59.873 --> 09:01.039
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:01.041 --> 09:03.008
-33 YEARS, FOR CRYING OUT LOUD.
-YEAH.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.944
HEY, ONE THING, ONE THING --
I WOULD LOVE TO KEEP THE RIGHTS

09:05.946 --> 09:07.379
-TO THE SONGS I WROTE.
-YEAH

09:07.381 --> 09:09.548
-OH, YEAH, SURE.
-NO, BUT I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT,

09:09.550 --> 09:11.483
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT
ABOUT IT.

09:11.485 --> 09:13.685
DON'T MAKE ME BEG!
I JUST WANT MY SONGS.
NO, NO, WE DON'T WANT THEM.

09:13.687 --> 09:16.187
YOU KNOW YOU REALLY
CHANGED MY LIFE TODAY.

09:16.189 --> 09:20.458
MAY YOU REALIZE BUDDHAHOOD
IN THIS LIFE.

09:20.460 --> 09:21.593
[ SIGHS ]

09:21.595 --> 09:22.861
OH.

09:22.863 --> 09:25.730
I GUESS I WON'T BE
NEEDING THIS ANYMORE.

09:29.468 --> 09:30.869
YEAH!
PUT ME ON THE BOARD!

09:30.871 --> 09:33.104
PUT ME ON THE GODDAMN BOARD!
I'M BACK, BABY!

09:33.106 --> 09:34.673
-WHAT?
-YOU GOT HER TO SIGN?

09:34.675 --> 09:35.974
ON THE LINE
THAT IS DOTTED!

09:35.976 --> 09:37.576
WELL, I GOT HER
TO SIGN, TOO.

09:37.578 --> 09:38.877
-SO DID I.
-ME, TOO.

09:38.879 --> 09:40.378
WHAT?

09:40.380 --> 09:41.446
MITTLEMAN!

09:41.448 --> 09:42.747
-MITTLEMAN!
-YES?

09:42.749 --> 09:45.216
CAT BLACK?
WE CAN'T SELL THIS CRAP.

09:45.218 --> 09:46.484
WE NEED THE GOOD LEADS.

09:46.486 --> 09:47.852
OH, THE LEADS
ARE THE LEADS.

09:47.854 --> 09:49.087
"THE LEADS ARE THE LEADS."
WHAT KIND OF --

09:49.089 --> 09:50.755
HE COMES IN HERE,
TALKS TO US

09:50.757 --> 09:52.190
LIKE WE'RE SOME SORT OF --
SORT OF...
EXACTLY.

09:52.192 --> 09:54.926
SY, YOU, WHAT IS IT EXACTLY
THAT YOU DO HERE?

09:54.928 --> 09:56.628
I'M TRYING TO RUN
A CHAPEL!

09:56.630 --> 09:59.798
WHO TOLD YOU
YOU COULD WORK WITH MEN?

09:59.800 --> 10:01.933
OH, I WORK
WITH MEN AND WOMEN.

10:01.935 --> 10:04.636
I'M GONNA HAVE YOUR JOB,
SHITHEAD.

10:05.404 --> 10:07.639
♪♪

10:07.641 --> 10:09.908
HEY, YOU GOING RELIGIOUS
ON US, CAT?

10:09.910 --> 10:12.310
I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE.
PROBABLY NOT.

10:12.312 --> 10:13.578
ANYWAY, THAT'S MY STORY.

10:13.580 --> 10:15.447
HEY, I HEARD YOU WERE
IN THE BAND X?

10:15.449 --> 10:17.048
OH.

10:17.050 --> 10:19.951
YOU KNOW, THAT IS THE FIRST TIME
THAT ANYONE HAS EVER SAID TO ME,

10:19.953 --> 10:22.220
"HEY, I HEARD YOU WERE
IN THE BAND X." THANKS, CAT.

10:22.222 --> 10:24.990
Cavett: <i> I'M HAPPY TO SAY</i>
<i>THAT WE HAVE WITH US RIGHT NOW</i>

10:24.992 --> 10:26.458
<i>A REAL MUSICAL LEGEND.</i>

10:26.460 --> 10:28.627
<i>LET'S HAVE A BIG</i>
<i>"CAVETT SHOW" WELCOME FOR X!</i>

10:28.629 --> 10:31.363
OH! [ LAUGHS ]

10:31.365 --> 10:34.899
♪♪

10:35.468 --> 10:40.105
♪ NO ONE IS UNITED ♪

10:40.107 --> 10:42.340
♪ AND ALL THINGS ARE UNTIED ♪

10:42.342 --> 10:45.210
